    <title>To amend title 38, United States Code, to provide for the inclusion of certain additional periods of active duty service for purposes of suspending charges to veterans' entitlement to educational assistance under the laws administered by the Secretary of Veterans Affairs during periods of suspended participation in vocational rehabilitation programs.</title>
    <originChamber>House</originChamber>
    <updateDate>2018-08-28T20:17:24Z</updateDate>
    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 164, Number 62 (Tuesday, April 17, 2018)]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. PETERS:H.R. 5538.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8[Page H3396]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
